## Pikaptcha Fake Catptcha Attack Analysis


# Overview:
The objective of this lab is the understanding and analysis of a Fake Captcha attack. The lab essentially teaches us how to detect suspicious behaviour logged into the system and then trace it back to the source, i.e. the fake captcha.
The scenario states: “Happy Grunwald contacted the sysadmin, Alonzo, because of issues he had downloading the latest version of Microsoft Office. He had received an email saying he needed to update, and clicked the link to do it. He reported that he visited the website and solved a captcha, but no office download page came back. Alonzo, who himself was bombarded with phishing attacks last year and was now aware of attacker tactics, immediately notified the security team to isolate the machine as he suspected an attack. You are provided with network traffic and endpoint artifacts to answer questions about what happened.”

